References for Adapter Pattern:

When to use Adapter Design Pattern:

1. When we want an object to use an existing incompatible interface.
2. When we need a mechanism for two existing incompatible interfaces/classes to talk
to each other.
3. When we want to create a middle layer for creating a connection from b/w your modern
code and existing legacy code.
4.When we want to create a middle layer for creating a connection from b/w your modern
code and 3rd-party code.

1. https://www.javadevjournal.com/java-design-patterns/adapter-design-pattern/
2. https://dzone.com/articles/adapter-design-pattern-in-java
